        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 1:25PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 125 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a broken line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles northeast of Gillham to 10
miles west of De Queen, or extending from 12 miles west of Umpire to
10 miles west of De Queen, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Horatio, Gillham, Geneva, West Line, West Otis and
Lebanon.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
